### Local persistence (never commit real photos or local DB data) ###
data/

### Model-eval harness — personal photos, gold labels, and generated reports stay local ###
eval/tagging/images/
eval/tagging/gold.json
eval/tagging/out/

### Git worktrees (isolated per-issue checkouts) ###
.worktrees/

### Lavish review artifacts (generated HTML review surfaces) ###
.lavish/

### Terraform (terraform/bootstrap/) — state can hold the access-key secret ###
# Never commit state; it is the biggest credential-leak risk for the bootstrap.
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
.terraform/
crash.log
crash.*.log
# tfvars may hold secrets/account-specific values; the committed module needs none.
*.tfvars
*.tfvars.json
# Saved plan files embed resolved values (incl. anything sensitive a plan reads).
*.tfplan
tfplan*.out
# Keep the provider lock file committable for reproducible plans.
!.terraform.lock.hcl

### AWS credential files (belong in ~/.aws or a git-ignored .env, never the repo) ###
.aws-credentials
aws-credentials
credentials.csv
